Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Suspended particles- sunny- light wind- water brackish.
Loon and eagle sighted- algae blooms on 7/10 and 8/1.
5 otters swimming- diving- and feeding together.
After two weeks of hard rain- total of 8"...bloom in water.
Small amounts of green algae near shore.  Particles in the water.
Sunny no wind- small particles in the water.
Rained last night and early morning.
A lot of green particles suspended in the water- clear- sunny day.
Algae is blooming and it drizzled all day Saturday the 26th.
Weather is overcast- loon with 2 young.
Clear- sunny and windy- algal bloom.
Cloudy- green algal bloom on the surface by the shoreline.
Green particles suspended in water- partly sunny.
Cloudy and rain.  Cold and windy.
Sun and wind.  Sulfur smell at 30 and 38 feet.
Calm- bright + sunny. High water. Loons.
Sky mostly clear- moderately breezy- and three gulls were only wildlife sighted this afternoon.
Clear- blue sky- faint breeze- 12 ducks in bay yesterday- and the water in bay has thick algae and floating seaweed- a putrid color.
Cloudless blue sky- slight breeze- and two muskrats sighted when leaving dock.
Cloudless blue sky- calm water- two waterfowl sighted- and algae and floating seaweed on still water in bay.
Partly cloudy- calm- beautiful day- 73 degrees
Clear sky- slight breeze. Saw 3 loons
Overcast- dead calm. Some algae bloom
Algae bloom in bay. Partly cloudy. Calm
Clear- breezy. Some algae bloom in protected bay
Wind from south- light breeze and clear sky. Water in bay is peasoup. 2 ducks in reeds on south side of lake
Partly cloudy- calm- algae in protected bay
Clear- calm- 72 F. Saw loon near test site.  No anchor needed.
Partly cloudy - slight breeze.  Needed anchor.  Loon near test site.
Sunny - breezy.  Observed loon on the way.
Partly cloudy- calm- temperature 71 degrees F.
Overcast- slight breeze.  Sighted 3 loons on lake.
Overcast- slight breeze- saw 5 loons flocking on lake
Clear- Water surface temperature 54 degrees- saw one loon on lake.
Partly cloudy- calm.  Air temperature 61 degrees
Mostly sunny- breezy.  Water surface temperature 71 degrees.  Air temperature 79 degrees
Sunny- Calm  Water temperature at surface 82 degrees
Calm- partly cloudy.  Saw one loon on the way to deep hole.
Sunny- Breezy. Heavy rain at 5:00 AM.  Surface water and air temperature 76 degrees.
Partly cloudy- breezy.  Surface temp. 69 degrees.  Air temp. 57 degrees.
Overcast- breezy.  Water surface temperature 69 degrees
Clear- Breezy.  Water surface temperature 67 degrees.
Clear- sunny- calm.  Water surface temperature 59 degrees
Clear- calm.  Water temperature 57 degrees.  Air temperature 59 degrees.
Partly cloudy- Surface temperature 54 degrees.  Air temperature 50 degrees
Partly cloudy- calm.  Saw two adult loons with two chicks.  First sighting of chicks on South Turtle in three years.  Good sign.
Sunny- windy.  Saw 1 adult loon with 1 chick
Sunny- clear and calm.  Saw 2 gulls
Clear- breezy.  Some algae bloom in bays.
Clear and calm.  Saw two loons and one blue herron.  Some algae bloom in bays.
Mostly sunny- slight breeze- surface temperature 70 degrees.  Air temperature 82 degrees
Air Temperature 70 degrees.  Partly cloudy- calm.
Clear and calm. Some algae in bays. Observed one loon on lake.
Cloudy- slight breeze- saw 2 adult loons Cloudy- slight breeze- saw 2 adult loons
Loon still on nest.  Weather cloudy- calm.
Saw loon with 1 chick.  Bright sun- slight breeze
Saw 2 loons with one chick.  Sunny- calm.
Saw loons with chick.  All diving but chick still being fed.Clear bright day.
Mother loon and chick at north end of lake.
Clear and sunny.  Observed one loon just off big island.
Heavy algae bloom in bay at south end of lake.  Adult loons apparently gone.  One of this years hatched loons still on lake
1 loon  south end of lake. nesting mate on small island net high on bank
1 loon nesting south end of lake on small island.  Mate nearby. Nest on north end island abandoned.  One egg in shallow water below nest.
2 loons on south end of lake
Ostracods present in zebra mussel veliger tow.--Shelby Kail
Eagle nesting on south end of lake.  Clear- sunny some haze.
Eagle nesting south end of lake.  Clear sunny some haze.
Eagle on nest lower South Turtle. Two adult loons at north end + 1 baby. Lone loon at south end.  Eagle at nest.  Clear + sunny
Loon family at north end of lake.  Clear sunny.  Eagle chick out of nest at south end of lake.
Mother and baby loon at north end of lake.
Adult loons gone.  Only this year's chicks are on the lake.
